The short silent film The Last Cartridges depicts an incident in this battle in which
Arsene Lambert’s men defended a retreat from within a house in Bazeilles [bah-zay]. In
this battle, Alexandre (+) Ducrot [do-crow] took over command from the injured Marshal
MacMahon. Having lost this battle, the Army of Chˆalons [sha-lone] was prevented from
relieving the Siege of (*) Metz and the losing emperor was captured. Helmuth von Moltke led the
victorious army in, for the point, what decisive battle in which Napoleon III was captured and his Second
French Empire was overthrown?=====
Battle of Sedan
